Don’t be fooled by the sometimes long wait, the food here is simply AMAZING! It’s one of the best Thai places around. My first time coming there, it was a BUSY night and because i ordered a little late, I anticipated a bit of a wait. I returned some minutes later only to antsy patrons waiting impatiently for their orders. Before I continue, i just want to say -don’t be that AHole at any restaurant who orders late and expect your food in less than 10 minutes! People are so annoyingly privileged. Nonetheless, i waited patiently for my food until the moment came and to my surprise, Bosslady put an extra plate of Pad Thai in my order to make up for the wait. Highly unnecessary but greatly appreciated! The dishes were incredible and made to perfection. It almost took me back to Thailand! Thank you all for your hard work during these difficult times!

My wife and I used to frequent a branch of Sala Thai that was located in Clarendon, but became victim to development. We were close to this location on Sunday and decided to stop in. It's great. We ordered Ka Prow and a chicken/peanut sauce combination. Ka Prow is normally a very spicy "three-pepper" rated dish. We scaled it back on pepper, and that really is fine, even for people like us who go for spicy. Three peppers at Sala Thai requires some acclimation. So, highly recommended to all, and not a noisy place. One nice touch was that the hostess gave us an extra container of rice to take home with the leftovers...and they were still great the next day!

We had a very nice dinner at Sala Thai while working in Bethesda.  We really had a hard time picking a place to eat because there are so many options, but we are glad we picked here.  It was a cold night and we came in after walking the capital mall and taking the Metro back to Bethesda.  We were chili, but when we walked in there was live jazz music, an inviting atmosphere, and a welcoming staff.  I started with the Tom Kah soup to warm up.  The soup had great flavor and had all the right ingredients in it to make it authentic.  Make with lemongrass and kafir lime leaves, this was a great way to start our meal.  The group of people I was with, was not into eating family style like I normally do so I had the drunken noodles because they are also so pleasing and fulfilling.  These noodles were perfect, great flavor, nice spice, and not over sauced.  I enjoyed them very much.  I also had a chance to try a daily special which was a pumpkin curry which also was delicious.  We had a great meal and the staff was helpful and friendly.  A great experience overall.
